<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1328">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/336g</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW2" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-04">
                                <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1914</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>55. Department’s telegram to-day regarding Red Cross ship <persName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Hamburg</hi></persName>. Request Foreign Office to
                            instruct German Consul, New York, to give up <persName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Hamburg’s</hi>
                            </persName> papers so that she may dear. He refuses to give up papers
                            without authority. Report immediately.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>